properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 17 at 8:25AM MST until January 17 at 1:00PM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
A disturbance will bring gusty winds and a wintry mix of
precipitation to south central South Dakota this morning.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. Additional snow accumulations of up
to one inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze. Winds
gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Mellette County and Todd County.

* WHEN...Until 2 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
